canonical:
  title: 冬至太一靑詞
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 變化無方常善救物吉㐫不僭職竟由人苟傾祈叩之誠卽荷畀矜之賜伏念以予過擧召厥咎徵當盛寒之戒時有恒燠之爲沴况雰霧崇朝而閉塞或雨潦連日以浸淫寔深兢灼之懷佇借高明之佑伏望陰陽常順無冬愆夏伏之災符瑞竝臻有天降地升之貺
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 冬至太一靑詞
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 變化無方。常善救物。吉㐫不僭。職竟由人。苟傾祈叩之誠。卽荷畀矜之賜。伏念以予過擧。召厥咎徵。當盛寒之戒時。有恒燠之爲沴。况雰霧崇朝而閉塞。或雨潦連日以浸淫。寔深兢灼之懷。佇借高明之佑。伏望陰陽常順。無冬愆夏伏之災。符瑞竝臻。有天降地升之貺。
korean:
  title: 동지 태일 청사
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 변화는 일정한 방향이 없으나 항상 만물을 잘 건져 주고, 길함과 융함은 거짓이 없으나 다만[職] 필경은 사람에게 달려 있는 법이옵니다. 진실로 빌고 조아리는 정성을 기울이면 바로 도와주고 어여삐 여겨 주시는 은혜를 받을 것이옵니다. 엎드려 생가하건대, 나의 지나친 처사 때문에 나쁜 징조를 불러 들여 한겨울 추위를 걱정해야할 때인데도 항상 따뜻한 음사(陰邪)가 있사옵니다. 더욱 자욱한 안개는 아침 나절이 지나도록 앞이 캄캄하게 끼어있고, 어떤 때는 장마비가 와 몇 날을 계속하여 젖어 있으니, 진실로 두려움이 깊어 높고 밝으신 도움을 빌리기 바랍니다. 음양이 항상 순조로와 겨울에 잘못되어 하복(夏伏)외 재앙이 없게 하고, 천부(天符)와 상서(祥瑞)삼광(三光)가 동시에 이르러 하늘의 기운은 내려오고, 땅의 기운은 올라오는 복을 주시기를 엎드려 바라옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1180_010_0080&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Blue Petition to the Great One on the Winter Solstice
  author: Lee Gyou-bo
  language: eng
  text: Transformation has no fixed pattern, yet it ever excels at delivering all creatures from harm. Fortune and misfortune do not deceive, and yet all outcomes rest finally upon human conduct. Should one offer sincere prayers and earnest supplication, then aid and compassionate grace shall surely follow. I humbly reflect that through my excessive transgressions, I have invited calamitous omens. In this season when winter's severity should reign, there persists instead an unseasonable warmth—a baleful anomaly. Moreover, thick mists cloak the morning, obscuring all before us, while in other times relentless rains fall for days, soaking the earth and my heart alike with profound dread. I humbly beseech your lofty brilliance for protection. May yin and yang remain ever in harmony, free from winter's failures and summer's calamities. May celestial tokens and auspicious signs converge together, with heaven's breath descending and earth's breath ascending to bestow their blessings.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This is a blue petition (청사), a formal prayer addressed to celestial powers for the rectification of natural and human affairs.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Great One on the Winter Solstice' (태일) refers to a celestial deity associated with cosmic harmony and the winter solstice turning point.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem reflects the medieval Korean belief in the correspondence between moral conduct and natural phenomena—that the poet's own failings have disrupted the proper seasonal order.
